1.title: Movin' on Up
1.plot: Angela, Vanessa, and Jessica finally move into their fly new house - but there's trouble in paradise when Vanessa and Angela fight over the master bedroom. And Angela hatches a secret plan for her childhood friend to move in.

2.title: In the Dawg House
2.plot: Angela and Danielle adopt a cat and a dog from an animal shelter, not knowing that Vanessa's boyfriend is allergic. Will the new pets cost Vanessa and her boyfriend their relationship?

3.title: Bummer Camp
3.plot: Lynn convinces Angela and Vanessa that a camping trip will help them relax. But four city girls in the woods? Look out! Back at the homestead Jessica confronts Danielle and things become heated.

4.title: Mousewarming Party
4.plot: Angela, Vanessa and Jessica throw a housewarming party, and everything's great until they discover the house is infested with mice! Angela freaks out and threatens to leave the house forever, so Vanessa and Jessica quickly track down an exterminator.

5.title: Model Behavior
5.plot: Vanessa is conflicted when Lynn wants to model for an important Pastry fashion show and Shawna takes Jessica to a Jewish singles night.

6.title: Turning the Tables
6.plot: Angela decides she wants to be a DJ but won't admit that she's bitten off more than she can chew. So Vanessa, Jessica and Brian teach her a lesson.

7.title: Hoop-LA
7.plot: Angela and Vanessa land a huge interview to promote Pastry but are shocked to find the interview has been mysteriously cancelled. Jessica crushes on one of the guys at her weekly pickup game.

8.title: What's in Store
8.plot: The girls all receive exciting life opportunities that may take them away from each other, and throw their new retail store into jeopardy. Rev bonds with Vanessa?s boyfriend Mike.

1.title: New Beginnings
1.plot: Vanessa and Angela have finally made the leap of faith, and settled permanently in Los Angeles! Vanessa takes Angela on a mountain hike to get the lay of the land - and to snap her out of the funk she's in about her recent painful breakup with TK.

2.title: Sherlock Homey
2.plot: When Jessica spills the beans to Vanessa and Angela that Aliceia met her ex-boyfriend, Raymond for coffee, the Simmons Sisters remind her of one of their sacred rules.

3.title: Have Your Pastry and Eat It Too
3.plot: The identity of Pastry hangs in the balance when Vanessa and Angela must choose between making a nightclub appearance or speaking to a troop of Girl Scouts. Complicating things, Jessica gets her hopes up that the sisters will choose the profitable nightclub gig so they can finally buy her a company car.

4.title: Rev's Angels
4.plot: While out shopping with Jessica, Angela becomes enamored with a hot pair of motorcycle boots. Angela loves the motorcycle mama look and along with Jessica becomes infatuated with motorcycle apparel.

5.title: Birthday Presence
5.plot: Up against a tight deadline to create recipes inspired by their Pastry shoe line, the girls worry about missing their Daddy's birthday. And Jessica recruits Alycia to help her with the hardest job ever - finding the perfect personal assistant for the Simmons Sisters.

6.title: Keepin' It Real Estate
6.plot: The Simmons Sisters decide to buy their first place in L.A., where they can put down roots and Jessica can finally have her own room. But are they ready to make the biggest commitment of their lives? Meanwhile, Jessica is eating like Michael Phelps in her quest for a big ol' booty, but Alycia's out to prove Jessica doesn't need to gain weight.

imdb.plot outline: We watched Rev Run's daughters grow up on MTV's Run's House. Now watch them come of age in Daddy's Girls. Picking up where Run's House left off, Daddy's Girls follows the exploits of Vanessa and Angela Simmons navigating their way through the fast lane of Hollywood, all while applying the valuable moral lessons their Daddy instilled in them. As Rev's girls acclimate to their new city, Vanessa and Angela take the critical steps in setting up a permanent residence in Los Angeles, including setting up west coast operations of their Pastry shoe line. Although Vanessa and Angela enjoy an exciting socialite lifestyle, they still face the same issues and challenges as other young women their age. Between dating problems, friend dynamics, and catfights, there is never a dull moment in their lives. The Rev knows his daughters are growing up and he has to let them mature in to young independent women, but to the Rev, they will always be Daddy's Girls.
